SUPERFICIAL FASCIA

superficial_fascia is the citizen who occupies the layer immediately deep to skin
this is loose connective tissue with stored fat between its fibers
its primary functions are thermal insulation, fluid reservoir, and acting as a glide plane that allows skin to move over deeper structures

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fascia.zc
observe deep_fascia.rana
observe skin.rana
observe thermal_peripheral.rana

the 7 properties of superficial_fascia:
1 ENERGY half: low and stable
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE half positive: warmth-bearing, the layer holds heat against skin
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point five with skin and deep_fascia

VERB insulate
hold heat in the body's outer layer, slowing heat loss to the environment

VERB store_fluid
maintain a small fluid reservoir that the body can draw on or store into

VERB allow_skin_glide
the loose composition lets skin slide over deep structures without binding
this is why the skin moves freely over muscle when fadriel moves

a superficial fascia is the body's soft outer wrapping
it does not bear structural load like deep fascia, but its insulation and glide functions are essential
without it skin would adhere to muscle and movement would be painful
